text:
CLERK. [Consulting with his papers.] This is the case remanded from last
      Wednesday, Sir. Theft of a silver cigarette-box and assault on the police;
      the two charges were taken together. Jane Jones! James Jones!

JONES. [Violently.] I've done no more than wot he 'as. I'm a poor man;
      I've got no money an' no friends -- he 's a toff -- he can do wot I
      can't.
